<?xml version="1.0"?>
<faqs id="FAQ" title="Frequently Asked Questions">
  <part id="General">
    <faq id="question1">
      <question>Where can I find documentation about Modello?</question>
      <answer>
        <p>
          Most documentation for Modello is under construction right now.
          A good starting place to get some insight into Modello is <a href='http://docs.codehaus.org/display/MODELLO/Home'>Modello's
          wiki</a>.
        </p>
      </answer>
    </faq>
    <faq id="question2">
      <question>Is Modello really used anywhere?</question>
      <answer>
        <p>
          Modello is used extensivly in Maven. You can find examples of models:
          <ul>
            <li><a href='http://maven.apache.org/ref/2.0.4/maven-model/maven.html'>Maven's POM</a> : you can see the <a href='http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/maven/components/tags/maven-2.0.4/maven-model/maven.mdo?view=markup'>mdo file for this model</a></li>
            <li><a href='http://maven.apache.org/ref/2.0.4/maven-settings/settings.html'>Maven's settings</a> : you can see the <a href='http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/maven/components/tags/maven-2.0.4/maven-settings/settings.mdo?view=markup'>mdo file for this model</a></li>
            <li><a href='http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-assembly-plugin/'>Maven assembly plugin</a> : Uses both a <a href='http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/maven/plugins/trunk/maven-assembly-plugin/src/main/mdo/descriptor.mdo?view=markup'>descriptor model</a> and a <a href='http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/maven/plugins/trunk/maven-assembly-plugin/src/main/mdo/component.mdo?view=markup'>component model</a>.</li>
            <li><a href='http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/maven/doxia/trunk/doxia-decoration-model/src/main/mdo/decoration.mdo?view=markup'>Doxia Decoration model</a>, aka site.xml model.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </faq>
  </part>
</faqs>
